<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7141852>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Tumerozetes roughleyi sp. nov. (a) dorsal aspect; (b) ventral aspect); (c) lateral aspect; (d) detail of seta le. Scale bar = 100 μm" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7141852/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7141862>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Sacculella yarra gen. et sp. nov. (a) palp; (b) chelicera; (c) digitus mobilis of chelicera, ventral aspect; (d) tutorium and sub-tutorium. Nodocepheus luxtoni sp. nov. (e) chelicera; (f) palp; (g) apex of rutellum; (h) tutorium and sub-tutorium; (i) rostrum and rostral setae; (j) Polypterozetes cherubin Grandjean, 1959, chelicera; (k) Podopterotegaeus miyamaensis Fujikawa, 2008, chelicera; (l) Nodocepheus dentatus Hammer, 1958, chelicera. Scale bars: a, b, d, e, f, h = 20 μm; i = 10 μm; c, g = 5 μm" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7141862/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7141854>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Tumerozetes roughleyi sp. nov. (a) anterior aspect; (b) bothridia and interlamellar plates; (c) waxy tegument on rostrum; (d) chelicera; (e) palp; (f) rutellum; (g) anal and genital plates; (h) bothridium. Scale bars: a–c, g, h = 50 μm; e, f = 15 μm" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7141854/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

